&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kimball Equipment Company is a leading provider of heavy equipment, parts, and services for the aggregate and mining industry. Established in 1946, we are a third-generation family-owned business with 13 locations across the western United States. We pride ourselves on our commitment to excellence, customer service, and our core values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Service Operations Coordinator is responsible for supporting the service department by managing administrative functions, coordinating service orders, and facilitating communication between customers, technicians, and internal departments. This role plays a key part in delivering a high-quality service experience to our customers through prompt, professional, and accurate communication and documentation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Open, process, and close service work orders promptly and accurately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Communicate with customers regarding service status updates, job estimates, scheduling, and follow-ups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Collaborate with the service team, parts department, and Service Manager/General Manager to ensure timely completion of jobs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Maintain accurate records of labor hours, parts usage, and service reports.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Process and submit invoices and warranty claims efficiently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Ensure a high level of customer satisfaction through timely and professional communication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Assist in ordering parts and coordinating logistics as needed for service jobs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Support the Management group with reporting, scheduling, and departmental goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Maintain a customer-focused approach, handling issues with urgency, empathy, and attention to detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· High school diploma or equivalent required; associate degree preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· 2+ years of administrative or customer service experience, preferably in a service, automotive, agricultural or heavy equipment industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Strong customer service skills with a professional and courteous demeanor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Excellent written and verbal communication abilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· High attention to detail and strong organizational skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Proficiency with Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Excel, Outlook).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Familiarity with ERP systems or service management software is a plus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Ability to multitask and prioritize in a fast-paced, team-oriented environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Knowledge of heavy equipment, parts, or technical services is preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working Conditions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Office environment with periodic exposure to the shop or yard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Frequent communication via phone and email with customers and technicians.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Must be able to sit, stand, and use a computer for extended periods.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

